Kenya’s Williamson Tea Posts Higher as Sales Increase

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-06-20T12:50:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/kenya-s-williamson-tea-posts-higher-as-sales-increase-1-.html
Williamson Tea Kenya Ltd., a
producer of the leaves, said full-year profit rose 1 percent as
sales increased.  Net income climbed to 884.4 million shillings ($9.7
million) in the 12 months through March, from 876 million
shillings a year earlier, according to a statement e-mailed by
the  Nairobi Stock Exchange  today. Revenue grew 21 percent to
3.28 billion shillings, it said.  The company’s directors have recommended a final dividend
of 12.50 shillings per share in addition to an interim dividend
of 2.50 shillings paid in January, it added.  Williamson Tea’s stock jumped 4.3 percent to 219 shillings,
the highest level since June 13, by the 3:00 p.m. close in the
capital, Nairobi.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 